text: Me First is the first album by indie band The Elected, released in 2004 via Sub Pop. It is a mix between indie and country. ==Track listing== All songs written by Blake Sennett, except where noted. #"7 September 2003" – 3:56 #"Greetings in Braille" – 3:58 #"My Baby's a Dick" – 3:31 #"A Time for Emily" – 2:23 #"Don't Get Your Hopes Up" – 3:30 #"Waves (The Time That You're Awake)" (Sennett, Blake Klugman) – 3:35 #"The Miles 'Til Home" – 5:10 #"Go On" – 5:17 #"C'mon, Mom" – 4:35 #"A Response to Greed" – 3:56 #"Don't Blow It" – 4:10 #"British Columbia" – 2:36 ==References== ==External links== *The Elected on MySpace Category:The Elected albums Category:2004 debut albums Category:Sub Pop albums
